We love the movement of this arrangement and the sheer fact it’s different. We ask our clients to discover their floral style preferences both in the context of the overall design and also separately standing alone. What do you gravitate towards? Does that style work well enough with the overall atmosphere we are creating? Do you like arrangements with some color blocking and flower type blocking as this one, or prefer all colors and flower types more scattered about. What about flowers pointing in different directions? And lastly, we love the hip vessel the flowers are in and the fact you see it a little. 
•
Gorgeous arrangement @astrodaphne 
•
Happy planning! 
•
#weddingplanning #weddingflowers #weddingdesign #floraldesign

We wanted to share our thoughts and feelings, and the response on stories has been significant.
•
If there is anything we have to learn at any time, we’re open for feedback. 
•
And no, we don’t have all the answers and we don’t know you or anyone better than you know yourselves. 
•
We have, however, learned a ton about ourselves, other people, family, relationships and marriage over the years in a different way that one does by being married. 
•
I can’t fathom being in the shoes of someone that is denied service for the color of their skin nor their sexual orientation. A new form of segregation, supported by law. •
#lgbtally #weddingplanner #sundaythoughts

Happy holiday ✨ let’s map out our year: kindness, gratitude, creativity and joy for 2024 
•
May you all unplug, get cozy and remember what life’s all about ❤️
•
Happy holiday week ahead ✨ the most wonderful time of the year no matter what or how you celebrate 
•
#holidays2023 #newyear2024 #peaceonearth #manifestpeace #manifestjoy #changeyourselfchangetheworld #love

•
2024
•
What if each morning we wake up with a special, well wrapped gift to unwrap. We take it in before we get up to have our first sip of coffee.
It’s our gift, we asked for it from the universe.
It’s time. It’s our very own time.
And we are the protagonist in our own story that takes place within this limited time, this gift of ours that cannot be replaced.
•
What if we lived each day as this gift we get to use. It’s not holier than thou, it’s healthily selfish. You put your attention to yourself, your gift of time, your challenges, joys, responsibilities, opportunities, and the noise subsides. That’s all. Other people’s mishegas evaporates for us.
•
Now we have to get up and do things for others, for our jobs, things we don’t want to do for ourselves even. If were doing them within our very own gift, how are we going to do them?
•
Less noise. Less distraction. More presence. More gratitude. More simplicity. More now moments. 
•
Beautiful photo by @alftown 
•
#snow #newyearseve #newyear #deepthoughts #peaceonearth #peaceinsideout #peace
